data.enText: a type of mint (= a plant used to give flavour to food that produces an oil with a strong flavour)
a sweet/candy flavoured with peppermint oil

tr: a candy flavored with peppermint oil
herb with downy leaves and small purple or white flowers that yields a pungent oil used as a flavoring

value.def: Peppermint is a strong, sharp flavouring that is obtained from the peppermint plant or that is made artificially.
A peppermint is a peppermint-flavoured sweet or piece of candy.
